<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="149" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,756,257,601]" box="[151,480,257,282]" pageId="15" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,292,257,281]" pageId="15" pageNumber="149">Description:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[299,354,260,282]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="149">Male</emphasis>
: Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,756,257,601]" pageId="15" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis box="[151,231,292,314]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="149">Female</emphasis>
: Body 
<quantity box="[332,437,289,313]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="15" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.40 mm</quantity>
long, reddish brown with darkened head and abdomen; antennae and legs reddish; palpi yellowish. Head with frons and occipital region slightly convex; frontal lobe short, separated from frons by shallow transverse sulcus. Antennae with scape and pedicel slightly longer than wide; antennomeres III- VIII wider than long; antennomere IX wider than VIII, distinctly wider than long; antennomere X wider than IX, distinctly wider than long; antennomere XI moderately elongate, shorter than VII-X combined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
